<subSubSection id="C331C195B74AFFF4F7B2F56CF900FBCC" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B94921EB74AFFF4F7B2F56CF765FD30" blockId="13.[2072,2666,2775,3203]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis id="B95F4E0CB74AFFF4F7B2F56CF77EFCA6" bold="true" box="[2073,2229,2775,2808]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74AFFF4F77FF56CF795FD41" authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Lepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">Lepus brasiliensis Linnaeus, 1758</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B439843B74AFFF4F7DAF545F765FD30" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3805018336" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">“in America meridionalis.” Restricted by O. Thomas in 1911 to “Pernambuco,” Brazil.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B94921EB74AFFF4F7B1F4CEF900FBCC" blockId="13.[2072,2666,2775,3203]" lastBlockId="13.[1459,2663,3208,3474]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74AFFF4F7B1F4CEF6F5FDC8" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[2074,2366,2933,2966]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">Sylvilagus brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74AFFF4F7B1F427F717FDE3" authorityName="Durant &amp; Guevara" authorityYear="2001" box="[2074,2268,2972,3005]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="varynaensis">S. varynaensis</taxonomicName>
. Formerly, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74AFFF4F62DF427F5F0FDE3" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[2438,2619,2972,3005]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">S. brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
included 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74AFFF4F723F47FF72DFDBB" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1932" box="[2184,2278,3012,3045]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dicei">S. dicei</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74AFFF4F69AF47FF652FDBB" baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[2353,2457,3012,3045]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gabbi">S. gabbi</taxonomicName>
as subspecies. Subspecies true: has been removed from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74AFFF4F7B1F3A9F706FA6D" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[2074,2253,3090,3123]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">S. brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
and now belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74AFFF4F651F3A9F5A9FA6D" baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[2554,2658,3090,3123]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gabbi">S. gabbi</taxonomicName>
. Taxonomic revision of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74AFFF4F62DF381F589FA05" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[2438,2626,3130,3163]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">S. brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
is necessary because some other subspecies might deserve full species status. As taxonomists are still trying to clarify the species differentiation in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BE99DB74AFFF4F883F314F864FA8E" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[1832,1967,3247,3280]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Sylvilagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sylvilagus</taxonomicName>
, the subspecific taxonomy is not elaborated yet. The original descriptions of the subspecies are often not very helpful as they are mostly based on few exterior characteristics and small numbers of individuals. It has been shown that the variability is clinal in more careful investigations. Hence, the distinction in subspecies might be arbitrary and unreasonable. Nineteen subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
